The paper discusses challenges in adaptive data analysis, which involves iteratively interacting with the same data set. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields in computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures (cs.DS), cryptography (cs.CR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper's focus on sample complexity and accuracy guarantees suggests that it is more likely to be categorized under cs.IT and cs.LG, but the use of error-correcting codes and concentrated uncertainty also point towards cs.CR and cs.DS.
